  "body": "Besu's implementation of EIP1559 is using a long instead of Uint256 for baseFee.  This is not likely to be a problem in the near future since baseFee would have to be in excess of 9 eth to cause an overflow, but we should match the types in the spec.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n* update implementation and tests to use Uint256 baseFee",
